Introduces students to the main principles of organization and financing of health care systems. The regulation, financing and provision of public health and health care services in Estonia will be studied. Performance of health care systems and services will be analyzed in the global context.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Develop basic knowledge on principles of organization, regulation, and financing of health care and public health systems. Develop a basic understanding of the assessment of health care services. To understand the dilemmas inherent to the provision of health services.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student will be expected: - to understand and explain the organization of public health and health care systems in different countries; - to explain the aim and implementation of reforms of health services and health care systems and to analyze these in the global context; - to understand the basics of health and economic impact assessment in clinical medicine and public health.
